Frontier — installation
=======================

Requirements
  Python 3.11+        engine + MCP server
  Node 18+            optional web UI (ui/)

Engine + MCP server
  git clone https://github.com/cafzal/frontier.git
  cd frontier
  pip install -e .    # installs all required Python dependencies (see pyproject.toml)

Run
  python -m mcp_server.server                       # stdio transport (local MCP clients)
  MCP_TRANSPORT=sse python -m mcp_server.server     # SSE transport, serves http://localhost:8000/sse

Verify
  pytest tests/

Optional third-party exact solvers
  pip install highspy   # HiGHS (CPU)  -> solve(solver="highs")
  pip install --extra-index-url=https://pypi.nvidia.com cuopt-cu12
                        # NVIDIA cuOpt (GPU) -> solve(solver="cuopt")
                        # https://github.com/NVIDIA/cuopt
                        # no GPU at hand? examples/cuopt_colab.ipynb is a ready Colab template

Optional web UI
  cd ui && npm install && npm run build && npm start
  # env vars and hosting: ui/README.md and README.md ("Deploy your own")

Full setup guide (hosted engine, MCP client snippets, deployment): README.md ("Setup").
